                                            h5 OpenStreetMap – global free editable map
                                            p I am a long-time contributor to the 
                                                a(href="https://openstreetmap.org/") OpenStreetMap
                                                | project. I not only participate in adding new data and updating existing information, but also put a lot of effort into localising tools and documentation into Ukrainian to attract more participants from Ukraine. I translated and maintained the interfaces of such editors as 
                                                a(href="https://ideditor.org/") iD
                                                | and 
                                                a(href="https://josm.openstreetmap.de/") JOSM
                                                |, translated the documentation in the OSM Wiki, and helped in the preparation of issues for the 
                                                a(href="https://weeklyosm.eu/uk") weeklyOSM
                                                |. In addition, I created a website for the 
                                                a(href="https://openstreetmap.org.ua") Ukrainian OpenStreetMap Community
                                                | and helped to establish cooperation with corporate users, one of whom created and maintains a tile server for use in Ukraine.
                                            p However, my efforts are not limited to the Ukrainian community. I have updated and offered to the community site that facilitates the wide dissemination of 
                                                a(href="https://andygol.co.ua/welcome-mat-osmf/") information about the project
                                                | and 
                                                a(href="https://andygol.co.ua/switch2osm-mkdocs/") Switch2OSM
                                                |, guidance on the transition to using OpenStreetMap.

                                            h5 3D Modeling and Printing
                                            p 3D printing became my hobby not long ago. I documented my first steps in this hobby on my 
                                                a(href="https://www.youtube.com/@AndriiHolovin") YouTube channel
